questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where your Spring Boot application's Metaspace is continuously growing until it throws an `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace`. You locate this class used for dynamic event routing: 

java
@Service
public class EventRoutingService {
    public void routeEvent(String tenantId, Event event) {
        ProxyFactory factory = new ProxyFactory(new DefaultEventHandler());
        factory.addAdvice(new TenantInterceptor(tenantId));
        EventHandler proxy = (EventHandler) factory.getProxy();
        proxy.handle(event);
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application's heap memory usage shows a slow, steady upward saw-tooth pattern that never returns to baseline, eventually leading to `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`. The heap dump reveals millions of `ThreadLocalMap$Entry` instances. You identify the following thread pool configuration and execution logic: 

java
public void process(UserRequest request) {
    taskExecutor.execute(() -> {
        contextHolder.set(new UserContext(request.getUserId()));
        doWork();
        // No cleanup performed
    });
}
